Ahrefs SEO Toolbar combines on-page SEO checker, broken link checker, link highlighter, redirect tracer, and country changer for search results in one add-on.

If you have a paid subscription with Ahrefs, you also get SEO metrics for the pages you visit and for the SERP results (with export).

***IMPORTANT NOTE***
This add-on does not give you free access to Ahrefs' metrics.
***

Here’s how Ahrefs SEO Toolbar can make your everyday SEO work easier:

1. On-page SEO report

When browsing any web page, click on the add-on icon or use a keyboard shortcut to open an on-page SEO report which includes:

- Title and Description (for JS-powered websites, you can compare tags in raw HTML and on the rendered version);
- Canonical URL;
- Indexability and crawlability (Robots Meta Tags, X-Robots-Tag, canonical tags);
- Headers and sub-headers structure of content;
- Word count;
- Social tags (Open Graph Tags and Twitter Cards);
- Images.

2. Link checker and link highlighter

Our add-on can read all the outgoing links on a page and highlight them based on the filters that you set:
External links;
Internal links;
Nofollow links;
UGC links;
Sponsored links;
Their combination.

3. HTTP header checker and redirect tracer

With Ahrefs SEO Toolbar, you can easily check HTTP response headers for the URL that you visit.

On top of that, this feature can help you track the redirects or redirect chains that took you to the destination URL. You can check HTTP response headers for every URL in a redirect.


***
User information handled by Ahrefs SEO Toolbar (only for Ahrefs subscribers):
- The page you’re browsing and its URL - to show you the relevant Page and Domain metrics and analyze its on-page data for you;
- Search query - to show you the relevant keyword data.

We do not store this information and will not disclose it.

